# RÉCOR Trivy ignore file
# =======================
#
# Consumed by the Trivy scan in `.github/workflows/publish-images.yaml`
# (ticket CI-2). Entries here suppress a specific HIGH or CRITICAL CVE
# from breaking the image-publish job.
#
# Format (one entry per line):
#
#   CVE-YYYY-NNNN  # <ticket>: <one-line rationale>; expires <YYYY-MM-DD>
#
# A `CVE-YYYY-NNNN` line on its own matches any path inside the image;
# pin to a specific dependency by appending `<package>` (see the Trivy
# docs for the path syntax).
#
# Doctrines:
#   D7 no workarounds — an entry here is an explicit acknowledgement
#                       that a HIGH/CRITICAL vulnerability is being
#                       *temporarily* suppressed. Every entry MUST
#                       reference an open ticket that tracks the real
#                       remediation, AND an expiry date no further
#                       than 30 days out. Entries without both are
#                       grounds for review rejection.
#   D14 fail-closed   — empty by default. Adding an entry weakens the
#                       gate; do so only with explicit reviewer
#                       sign-off and the runbook entry below updated.
#   D20 supply chain  — every override here is a public, version-
#                       controlled record. No silent suppressions.
#
# Procedure for adding an entry:
#   1. Open an issue describing the CVE, the affected dependency, the
#      attempted upstream fix, and why the fix is not yet viable.
#   2. Add a single line to this file with the ticket reference and an
#      expiry date in the comment.
#   3. Update docs/runbooks/supply-chain.md § "Active suppressions"
#      with the same information in a structured table.
#   4. Open a follow-up to remove the entry before the expiry date.
#
# See docs/runbooks/supply-chain.md for the full audit + override
# workflow.
#
# Active suppressions: (none)
